Ms Bishop's popularity has jumped from 11 per cent in June to 20 per cent.

But both the Foreign Minister and Prime Minister fall into second place behind Communications Minister Malcolm Turnbull who remains the overall choice with 35 per cent backing from voters.

The Fairfax poll of 1,401 people, carried out between Thursday and Sunday, found female voters heavily favoured Mr Turnbull or Ms Bishop.

